Subscription revenue changed the ecommerce game. Predictable monthly income, higher customer lifetime values, and reduced acquisition pressure — it's why every DTC brand now has a subscribe-and-save option. But managing subscriptions at scale is genuinely complicated. Failed payments, shipping modifications, pause requests, and churn prevention all require dedicated infrastructure.

Recharge has powered subscription programs for over 20,000 brands, processing billions in recurring revenue. But is it still the right choice in 2026, especially with newer competitors like Skio and Stay Ai gaining ground? Our team has implemented and managed Recharge across dozens of ecommerce operations, from single-product supplement brands to complex multi-SKU retailers. Here's what we've learned.

